commit.message: bump version to 0.10

fix error on "single: oneshot"

If the `single` status options is set to `oneshot`, it now gets parsed as
`True` instead causing an error.

bump hspec

this is entirely cosmetic (hspec resolves to the newest version
anyway), but versions over 2 are preferred so it's probably for
the best to make it explicit.
add github ci, remove travis ci
move unreleased changes to be under 0.10

remove deprecated functions

Remove `(<&>)`, `updateId`, `addList`, `playlistAddList`
add test for applicative pause command
`idle` now detects all subsystems

move `toggle` from Extentions to PlaybackControl

It corresponds to the now undeprecated "pause" command, including tests.
add missing `ReplayGainMode` constructor
add missing `Subsystem` constructors
add missing metadata tags

replace `(Position,Position)` with `Range`

Also adds support for partial ranges.

`list` now takes a general `Query`

Before it took a `Maybe Artist`, due to the way the mpd list command
worked before version 0.19.
require MPD version 0.19 or later
travis: bump ghc 8.10 to 8.10.3, stack lts to 16
